617.en_source: Video's a poor excuse, I know.

618.sl_source: Toda pomaga mi, da si zapomnim.
618.sl_trans: Vendar mi pomaga, da se spomnim.

620.sl_source: Včasih je tako veliko lepote na svetu.
620.en_source: Sometimes there's so much beauty in the world.
620.sl_trans: Včasih je na svetu toliko lepote.

621.sl_source: Počutim se, kot da je ne morem prenesti in moje srce se bo kar vdalo.
621.en_source: I feel like I can't take it and my heart is just going to cave in.
621.sl_trans: Zdi se mi, da tega ne morem več prenašati in da se mi bo srce zlomilo.

625.sl_source: Ne, je že v redu, ljubica.
625.en_source: No, that's quite all right, dear.
625.sl_trans: Ne, to je v redu, draga.

626.sl_source: Z očetom sva ravnokar razpravljala o njegovem dnevu.
626.en_source: Your father and I were just discussing his day at work.
626.sl_trans: S tvojim očetom sva se ravno pogovarjala o njegovem delovnem dnevu.

627.sl_source: Zakaj ne poveš še hčerki, dragi.
627.en_source: Why don't you tell our daughter about it, honey?
627.sl_trans: Zakaj o tem ne poveš najini hčerki, dragi?

628.en_source: Janie, today I quit my job.
628.sl_trans: Janie, danes sem dal odpoved v službi.

629.sl_source: Nato sem šefu povedal, naj se jebe in iz njega izsilil skoraj 60.000 dolarjev.
629.en_source: Then I told my boss to go fuck himself, and then I blackmailed him for almost $60,000.
629.sl_trans: Nato sem šefu rekel, naj se gre jesti, in ga izsiljeval za skoraj 60.000 dolarjev.

631.sl_source: Tvoj oče misli, da je tako obnašanje nekaj, na kar je lahko ponosen.
631.en_source: Your father seems to think this kind of behavior is something to be proud of.
631.sl_trans: Zdi se, da vaš oče meni, da je takšno vedenje nekaj, na kar je lahko ponosen.

632.sl_source: In tvoja mama bi raje videla, da živim kot zapornik.
632.en_source: And your mother seems to prefer that I go through life like a fucking prisoner.
632.sl_trans: Tvoja mati pa bi najraje videla, da živim kot zajebanec.

634.sl_source: In občudujem, kako si do mene lahko tako zaničevalen na isti dan, ko si izgubil svojo službo!
634.en_source: And I marvel that you can be so contemptuous of me on the same day that you lose your job!
634.sl_trans: In čudim se, da me lahko tako zaničuješ na isti dan, ko izgubiš službo!

636.sl_source: Ups, kam je pa šla moja služba?
636.en_source: It's not like, Whoops, where did my job go?
636.sl_trans: Ne gre za to, da bi rekel: Ups, kam je šla moja služba?

639.sl_source: Hvala, ker me postavljaš pod tak dodaten pritisk, da bom zdaj samohranilka.
639.en_source: And I want to thank you for putting me under the added pressure of being the sole breadwinner now.
639.sl_trans: Zahvaljujem se vam, da ste me še dodatno obremenili s tem, da sem zdaj edini hranilec družine.

642.sl_source: Ne obremenjuj se s tem, kdo bo odplačeval hipoteko.
642.en_source: Don't give a second thought as to who's going to pay the mortgage.
642.sl_trans: Ne razmišljajte o tem, kdo bo plačeval hipoteko.

644.sl_source: Boš zdaj ti poskrbela za vse, Carolyn?
644.en_source: You're going to take care of everything now, Carolyn?
644.sl_trans: Zdaj boš poskrbela za vse, Carolyn?

648.sl_source: Ti ni odveč, da boš sama nosila odgovornost?
648.en_source: You don't mind having the sole responsibility?
648.sl_trans: Vas ne moti, da ste edini odgovorni?

649.sl_source: Možu se je zahotelo pustiti službo.
649.en_source: Your husband feels he can just quit his job.
649.sl_trans: Vaš mož meni, da lahko preprosto pusti službo.

650.sl_source: Bi mi kdo prosim podal preklete beluše?
650.en_source: Will someone please pass me the fucking asparagus?
650.sl_trans: Naj mi nekdo podari jebene šparglje?

651.en_source: I'm not going to be a part of this.

653.sl_source: Dovolj mi je tega, da se obnašata, kot da ne obstajam.
653.en_source: I am sick and tired of being treated like I don't exist.
653.sl_trans: Dovolj mi je, da me obravnavajo, kot da ne obstajam.

654.sl_source: Vedve počneta karkoli kadarkoli, jaz pa se ne pritožujem.
654.en_source: You two do whatever you want to do whenever you want to do it, and I don't complain.
654.sl_trans: Počnita, kar hočeta in kadar hočeta, in jaz se ne pritožujem.

660.sl_source: Če se ne pritožuješ, kaj je potem to?
660.en_source: If you don't complain, what is this?
660.sl_trans: Če se ne pritožujete, kaj je to?

661.sl_source: Prinesimo smehometer in poglejmo, kako visoko bo prišel.
661.en_source: Yeah, let's bring in the laugh meter and see how loud it gets on that one.
661.sl_trans: Ja, vključimo merilnik smeha in poglejmo, kako glasen bo pri tem.

664.sl_source: Menjali bomo glasbo ob večerji, ker sem po pravici - in mislim, da nisem edini - utrujen od tega sranja Lawrenca Welka.
664.en_source: From now on, we're going to alternate our dinner music, because, frankly and I don't think I'm alone here I am really tired of this Lawrence Welk shit.
664.sl_trans: Odslej bomo glasbo za večerjo menjavali, ker sem, odkrito povedano, in mislim, da nisem sam, res naveličan tega sranja Lawrenca Welka.

668.sl_source: Glej, želim si, da danes ne bi videla te grozne scene.
668.en_source: Look, I wish that you hadn't witnessed that awful scene tonight.
668.sl_trans: Poglej, želim si, da danes ne bi bili priča temu groznemu prizoru.

669.sl_source: Toda na nek način sem vesela.
669.en_source: But in a way, I'm glad.
669.sl_trans: Toda na neki način sem vesel.

671.sl_source: Da sem videla kakšna norca sta z očetom v resnici?
671.en_source: So I could see what freaks you and Dad really are?
671.sl_trans: Da bi videl, kakšna čudaka sta v resnici ti in oče?

676.sl_source: Ne, vesela sem, ker ker si zdaj dovolj stara, da se naučiš najpomembnejše lekcije v življenju:
676.en_source: No, I'm glad because, uh because you're old enough now to learn the most important lesson in life:
676.sl_trans: Ne, vesela sem, ker si zdaj dovolj star, da se lahko naučiš najpomembnejše lekcije v življenju:

677.sl_source: Na nikogar se ne moreš zanesti, razen nase.
677.en_source: You cannot count on anyone except yourself.
677.sl_trans: Na nikogar se ne morete zanesti, razen nase.

678.sl_source: Na nikogar se ne moreš zanesti, razen nase.
678.en_source: You cannot count on anyone except yourself.
678.sl_trans: Na nikogar se ne morete zanesti, razen nase.

679.sl_source: Žalostno je, toda resnično, in prej kot to spoznaš, bolje je.
679.en_source: You know, it's sad but true, and the sooner you learn it, the better.
679.sl_trans: Veste, to je žalostno, a resnično, in čim prej se tega naučite, tem bolje.

680.sl_source: Glej, mami, ne zdi se mi pravi trenutek za razneženje.
680.en_source: Look, Mom, I really don't feel like having a Kodak moment here.
680.sl_trans: Mami, res se mi ne zdi, da bi se mi tu zgodil trenutek Kodak.

682.sl_source: Samo poglej, kaj vse ti nudim.
682.en_source: Just look at everything you have!

683.sl_source: Ko sem bila tvojih let, sem živela v stanovanju!
683.en_source: When I was your age, I lived in a duplex!
683.sl_trans: Ko sem bil star toliko kot ti, sem živel v dvostanovanjski hiši!

684.en_source: We didn't even have our own house.

688.sl_source: Ne, gospod, ne bom se tepel.
688.en_source: No, sir, I won't fight you.
688.sl_trans: Ne, gospod, ne bom se boril z vami.

690.en_source: How did you get in there?

692.en_source: What were you looking for, huh?

696.sl_source: Svoji punci sem hotel pokazati vaš nacistični krožnik.
696.en_source: I wanted to show my girlfriend your Nazi plate.
696.sl_trans: Svojemu dekletu sem želel pokazati tvojo nacistično ploščo.

701.sl_source: To je za tvoje dobro, fant.
701.en_source: This is for your own good, boy.
701.sl_trans: To je v tvoje dobro, fant.

702.sl_source: Nimaš spoštovanja do stvari drugih ljudi in do avtoritete.
702.en_source: You have no respect for other people's things and for authority.
702.sl_trans: Ne spoštujete stvari drugih ljudi in avtoritete.

705.sl_source: Ne moreš enostavno početi vsega, kar ti zapaše.
705.en_source: Can't just go around doing whatever you feel like.
705.sl_trans: Ne morete kar tako početi, kar se vam zahoče.

712.en_source: Thank you for trying to teach me.
712.sl_trans: Hvala, ker ste me poskušali naučiti.

714.en_source: Oh, Ricky, You stay out of there.
714.sl_trans: Oh, Ricky, ti se drži stran od tam.

715.sl_source: Moram reči, gospa Burnham, ko ste prvič prišla sem, sem mislil, da boste obupni, vendar vam gre odlično.
715.en_source: I gotta say, Mrs. Burnham, when you first came here, I thought you would be hopeless, but you're a natural.
715.sl_trans: Gospa Burnham, ko ste prvič prišli sem, sem mislil, da boste brezupni, a ste naravnost naravnost izurjeni.

716.sl_source: Vem samo, da obožujem streljanje s pištolo.
716.en_source: Well, all I know is I love shooting this gun.
716.sl_trans: Vse, kar vem, je, da rad streljam s to pištolo.

718.en_source: Uh, whose car is that out front?

720.sl_source: 1970 pontiac firebird, avto, ki sem si ga vedno želel in zdaj ga imam.
720.en_source: 1970 Pontiac Firebird, the car I've always wanted, and now I have it.
720.sl_trans: 1970 Pontiac Firebird, avto, ki sem si ga vedno želel, in zdaj ga imam.

725.sl_source: Se ne bi moral prej posvetovati z mano?
725.en_source: Shouldn't you have consulted me first?
725.sl_trans: Ali se ne bi morali najprej posvetovati z mano?

733.en_source: We have the whole house to ourselves.

735.en_source: When did you become so joyless?
735.sl_trans: Kdaj ste postali tako brez veselja?

738.sl_source: Veliko stvari se dogaja z mano, o katerih ničesar ne veš, gospod Pametnjakovič.
738.en_source: There happens to be a lot about me that you don't know, Mr. Smarty Man.
738.sl_trans: O meni je veliko stvari, ki jih ne veste, gospod Pametnež.

739.sl_source: V mojem življenju je veliko sreče.
739.en_source: There's plenty of joy in my life.
739.sl_trans: V mojem življenju je veliko veselja.

740.sl_source: Kaj se je zgodilo s tisto punco, ki je zaigrala napade na zabavah, če se je dolgočasila?
740.en_source: Whatever happened to that girl who used to fake seizures at frat parties when she got bored?
740.sl_trans: Kaj se je zgodilo z dekletom, ki je na bratskih zabavah uprizarjalo napade, ko ji je bilo dolgčas?

741.sl_source: Ki je tekla na streho najinega prvega stanovanja, da se je razkazovala prometnim helikopterjem?
741.en_source: Who used to run up to the roof of our first apartment building to flash the traffic helicopters?
741.sl_trans: Kdo je nekoč tekel na streho naše prve stanovanjske stavbe, da bi se oglasil pri prometnih helikopterjih?

742.en_source: Have you totally forgotten about her?

744.sl_source: Lester, pivo boš polil po kavču.
744.en_source: Lester, you're going to spill beer on the couch.
744.sl_trans: Lester, pivo boš polil na kavč.

747.sl_source: To je zofa za 4.000 dolarjev, tapecirana z italijansko svilo.
747.en_source: This is a $4,000 sofa, upholstered in Italian silk.
747.sl_trans: To je kavč za 4.000 dolarjev, oblazinjen z italijansko svilo.

748.en_source: This is not just a couch.

751.sl_source: To je samo stvar, in postala ti je bolj pomembna kot življenje.
751.en_source: This is just stuff, and it's become more important to you than living.
751.sl_trans: To so le stvari, ki so vam postale pomembnejše od življenja.

753.en_source: I'm only trying to help you!

757.en_source: I don't like how I look.
757.sl_trans: Ni mi všeč, kako sem videti.

760.sl_source: Ne bom sedela tu zaradi tega sranja.
760.en_source: I'm not going to sit here for that shit.
760.sl_trans: Ne bom sedel tukaj zaradi tega sranja.

766.sl_source: Povej mi, kako je biti v bolnišnici.
766.en_source: So tell me about being in the hospital.
766.sl_trans: Povejte mi, kako ste bili v bolnišnici.

767.sl_source: Ko sem bil star 15 let, me je oče videl kaditi travo.
767.en_source: When I was 15, my dad caught me smoking dope.
767.sl_trans: Ko sem bil star 15 let, me je oče ujel pri kajenju mamil.

768.sl_source: Totalno je znorel in se odločil, da me pošlje v vojaško šolo.
768.en_source: He totally freaked and decided to send me to military school.
768.sl_trans: Popolnoma se je prestrašil in se odločil, da me bo poslal v vojaško šolo.

769.sl_source: Saj sem ti pravil o redu in disciplini, ne?
769.en_source: I told you this whole thing about structure and discipline, right?
769.sl_trans: Povedal sem vam vse o strukturi in disciplini, kajne?

770.en_source: Of course, I got kicked out.

773.sl_source: In naslednji dan je nek sošolec nekaj pripomnil o mojih laseh in se mi je strgalo.
773.en_source: And the next day at school, some kid made a crack about my haircut, and I just snapped.
773.sl_trans: Naslednji dan v šoli je neki otrok izustil nekaj o moji frizuri, pa sem se kar zlomila.

775.sl_source: In bi ga ubil, če me ne bi potegnili z njega.
775.en_source: I would've killed him if they hadn't pulled me off.
775.sl_trans: Ubila bi ga, če me ne bi odnesli.

776.sl_source: Takrat me je oče poslal v bolnišnico.
776.en_source: That's when my dad put me in the hospital.
776.sl_trans: Takrat me je oče dal v bolnišnico.

777.sl_source: Nafilali so me z zdravili in me pustili tam dve leti.
777.en_source: They drugged me up and left me in there for two years.
777.sl_trans: Omamili so me in me tam pustili dve leti.

781.sl_source: Jaz bi svojega očeta gotovo sovražila, če bi mi naredil kaj takega.
781.en_source: Well, you'd better believe I'd hate my dad if he did something like that to me.
781.sl_trans: Verjemite, da bi sovražil svojega očeta, če bi mi storil kaj takega.

783.en_source: I already do hate my dad.

786.sl_source: Zatreskal se je v mojo prijateljico Angelo in to je ostudno.
786.en_source: He's got this crush on my friend Angela, and it's disgusting.
786.sl_trans: Zaljubljen je v mojo prijateljico Angelo in to je odvratno.

787.sl_source: Bi raje videla, da bi se vate?
787.en_source: You'd rather he had the crush on you.

790.sl_source: Toda bilo bi lepo, če bi mu bila vsaj tako pomembna kot ona.
790.en_source: But it'd be nice if I was anywhere near as important to him as she is.
790.sl_trans: Vendar bi bilo lepo, če bi bila zanj vsaj približno tako pomembna kot ona.

791.sl_source: Vem, da misliš, da je moj oče neškodljiv, toda motiš se.
791.en_source: I know you think my dad's harmless, but you're wrong.
791.sl_trans: Vem, da misliš, da je moj oče neškodljiv, vendar se motiš.

792.en_source: He's doing massive psychological damage to me.
792.sl_trans: Naredil mi je ogromno psihološko škodo.

794.sl_source: No, tudi jaz zdaj potrebujem red, malo preklete discipline.
794.en_source: Well, now I, too, need structure, a little fucking discipline.
794.sl_trans: No, zdaj tudi jaz potrebujem strukturo, malo jebene discipline.

796.sl_source: Kako naj mi ne bi škodoval?
796.en_source: How could he not be damaging me?
796.sl_trans: Kako mi ne bi mogel škodovati?

797.sl_source: Potrebujem očeta, ki bi mi bil vzor, ne pa tak pohoten fantek, ki si pošprica hlače takoj, ko pripeljem domov sošolko.
797.en_source: I need a father who's a role model, not some horny geek boy who's going to spray his shorts whenever I bring a girlfriend home from school.
797.sl_trans: Potrebujem očeta, ki mi bo za vzor, ne pa kakšnega pohotnega geeka, ki si bo poškropil hlače, kadarkoli bom iz šole pripeljal dekle.

799.sl_source: Nekdo bi mu moral skrajšati muke.
799.en_source: Someone really should just put him out of his misery.
799.sl_trans: Nekdo bi ga moral res rešiti njegove bede.

800.en_source: Want me to kill him for you?
800.sl_trans: Želiš, da ga ubijem namesto tebe?

804.sl_source: Varuška sem že od desetega leta.
804.en_source: I've been baby-sitting since I was about ten.
804.sl_trans: Otroke varujem že od svojega desetega leta.

806.sl_source: Seveda sem jih hranila za povečanje prsi.
806.en_source: Of course I was saving it up for a boob job.
806.sl_trans: Seveda sem jih varčevala za operacijo prsi.

807.sl_source: To ni ravno lepo najeti nekoga, da ti ubije očeta.
807.en_source: You know, that's not a very nice thing to do hiring someone to kill your dad.
807.sl_trans: Veste, to ni ravno lepo, če najamete nekoga, da vam ubije očeta.

808.sl_source: Potem pa nisem zelo dobro dekle, kaj?
808.en_source: Well, I guess I'm not a very nice girl then, am I?
808.sl_trans: No, mislim, da potem nisem preveč prijazno dekle, kajne?

809.sl_source: Saj veš, da ne mislim resno, ne?
809.en_source: You know I'm not serious, right?
809.sl_trans: Veš, da ne mislim resno, kajne?

811.sl_source: Sploh veš, kakšno srečo imava, da sva se našla?
811.en_source: You know how lucky we are to have found each other?
811.sl_trans: Veste, kakšno srečo imamo, da smo se našli?

812.sl_trans: Spomnite se tistih plakatov, ki so rekli.

813.sl_source: Danes je prvi dan preostanka vašega življenja?
813.en_source: Today is the first day of the rest of your life?
813.sl_trans: Danes je prvi dan preostanka tvojega življenja?

814.sl_source: To velja za vsak dan, razen za enega dneva, ko umreš.
814.en_source: Well, that's true with every day except the day you die.
814.sl_trans: To velja za vsak dan, razen za dan, ko umreš.

816.en_source: I've got a very important appointment.

817.sl_source: Mama, ali lahko Angela danes prespi tu?
817.en_source: Is it okay if Angela sleeps over tonight?
817.sl_trans: Je v redu, če Angela danes prespi pri nas?

819.sl_source: Mislila sem, da sta se skregali.
819.en_source: I thought you two had a fight.
819.sl_trans: Mislil sem, da sta se sprla.

820.en_source: I haven't seen her around here in a while.
820.sl_trans: Že nekaj časa je nisem videl tukaj.

822.sl_source: Preveč me je bilo sram, da bi jo pripeljala zaradi tebe in tvojega obnašanja.
822.en_source: I've been too embarrassed to bring her over, because of you and that way that you behave.
822.sl_trans: Bilo mi je preveč nerodno, da bi jo pripeljal k sebi, zaradi tebe in tvojega vedenja.

824.sl_source: Saj sem komaj kaj govoril z njo.
824.en_source: I've barely even spoken to her.

826.sl_source: Neprestano strmiš vanjo, kot da si pijan!
826.en_source: You stare at her all the time like you're drunk!
826.sl_trans: Ves čas jo gledaš, kot da si pijan!

828.sl_source: Raje se pazi, ali pa boš postala prasica kot tvoja mati!
828.en_source: You better watch yourself, or you're going to turn into a real bitch just like your mother!
828.sl_trans: Pazi nase, sicer boš postala prava mrha kot tvoja mati!

832.sl_source: Grem z Jane in njeno mamo.
832.en_source: I'm going with Jane and her mom.
832.sl_trans: Jaz grem z Jane in njeno mamo.

837.sl_source: Potrebujem Super Smeškota s sirom, takoj!
837.en_source: I need that Super Smiley with cheese ASAP!
837.sl_trans: Potrebujem ta Super Smiley s sirom čim prej!

838.en_source: You need more than that, my little hombre.
838.sl_trans: Potrebuješ več kot to, moj mali fantek.

843.sl_source: No, potem bova pa morala biti poredna, kaj?
843.en_source: Oh, well, then I guess we'll just have to be bad, won't we?
843.sl_trans: No, potem pa mislim, da bomo morali biti slabi, kajne?

844.sl_source: Prosim dvojni Smeškov sendvič, rebrast krompirček in vanilijev shake.
844.en_source: I'll have a Double Smiley sandwich, - curly fries and a vanilla shake.
844.sl_trans: Jaz si bom privoščil sendvič Double Smiley, krompirček in vanilijev koktajl.

847.en_source: Please drive up to the window.

849.sl_source: Mislim, da si danes zasluživa malo hitre hrane, po današnji telovadbi zjutraj.
849.en_source: I think we deserve a little junk food after the workout we had this morning.
849.sl_trans: Mislim, da si po jutranjem treningu zaslužimo malo nezdrave hrane.

855.sl_source: Bi poskusili našo govejo pito s sirom?
855.en_source: Would you like to try our new beef and cheese pot pie on a stick?
855.sl_trans: Želite poskusiti našo novo pito z govedino in sirom na palčki?

856.sl_source: Za samo 1,99 dolarja po znižani ceni.
856.en_source: Just $1.99 for a limited time only.

857.en_source: We were just at a seminar.

858.sl_source: Srečala sva se že, toda nekaj mi pravi, da si me boste tokrat zapomnili.
858.en_source: We've met before, but something tells me you're going to remember me this time.
858.sl_trans: Srečala sva se že prej, a nekaj mi govori, da si me boš tokrat zapomnila.

860.sl_source: To se vas res ne tiče.
